use Blue-Green Deployment
–	What is it ? 
·	How to maintain and guarantee the best running all the time. ? (99,99 availability?) 
It is very difficult to achieve 99.99% uptime, and reaching that level would require extremely high costs for a startup (multiple regions, multiple availability zones, complex deployment). It also depends on many external factors.
 To achieve 99.9% uptime, we can implement the following:
Load Balancers
·	2+ HAProxy/Nginx instances in Active–Passive mode
·	Keepalived with a Virtual IP for automatic failover
·	Health checks every 5 seconds
Application Servers (Nextcloud/Odoo/Keycloak)
·	Minimum 2 instances across 2 Availability Zones
·	Auto-scaling
·	Session persistence via a Redis cluster
Databases (PostgreSQL)
·	1 Primary + 1 Standby replica (minimum)
·	Synchronous replication for zero data loss
·	Streaming replication for real-time sync
Cache Layer (Redis)
·	Redis Sentinel with 2 nodes (1 master, 1 replica)
·	Automatic failover
·	Persistent storage for sessions
Storage
·	Object storage (S3/MinIO) with 2× replication
·	Distributed file system (Ceph/GlusterFS)
·	Never store data on a single disk
